          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A large coaxial Ge detector with a relative",
                "efficiency at 1332 keV of 110%. This detector was",
                "calibrated with a Physikalisch-Technische Bundestalt",
                "152Eu standard source (assayed in 1976) using",
                "the gamma-rays: 121.7, 344.3, 778.9, 964.0, 1085.8,",
                "1112.1, 1408.0 keV. Its efficiency curve was extended",
                "above 1400 to 2614 keV by counting a 232Th source",
                "using the gamma-rays: 583.2, 763.3, 785.5, 860.5,",
                "1620.7, 2614.5 keV. The relative peak efficiency",
                "curve from the 232Th source was normalized to the",
                "absolute curve from the 152Eu standard. From the",
                "uncertainties in the peak areas and those of the",
                "gamma-ray intensities, an uncertainty of +-5% between",
                "121 and 1400 keV and +-8% from 1400 to 2614 keV was",
                "assigned."
              ]
            }
          ],
